    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices with a rotating flat disc or turntable on which clay may be shaped to create symmetrical forms; the process of forming clay objects on a potter's wheel is throwing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047814/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045361/Savage and Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Ceramics (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000033441/Hamer, Potter's Dictionary (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具有旋轉淺盤或轉盤的設備，可將置於其上之黏土塑為對稱的形狀式；在陶輪上形塑陶器的過程，稱為拉坏。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
